reviews.review_text: This is really half SBD (and not half bad Jazz Dead) No one had reviewed this yet.  Maybe that's because it looks like it's an audience recording, but actually from Playin' thru the end it's pretty clean SBD.  The audience portion quality is pretty sketchy, so I only downloaded the SBD portion.  Giving it my first listen.  PITB is concise for the period.  China Rider gives us that beautiful feelin' grooveyesque transition jam. GSET typically hot for the period.  The jam out of Truckin' seems to be solidly into that early 73 jazz Dead phase, but it actually gets pretty quiet and moody, with some interesting piano work from Keith.  Eyes sounds great! Bottom line is that the second half is download-worthy for sure.
Damn Good Show! In my opinion this show has some of the HOTTEST 73' Keys!!! Amazing! This is a very fun and uplifting show! Take a listen.

Overlooked From playin in the band is sbd

The last half of the show is one of my favorites from 73
cumberland damn, this is an epic cumberland! wish there was soundboard of this show available but hey, the energy still comes through this somewhat muddied mix.

I was there I'm probably over-rating the show because I was there. First time hearing Eyes of the World and US Blues - studio versions were not released yet. This was a Friday night show and Saturday was Hot Tuna in the women's gym at SU. Incredible weekend of music!

Truckin' up to Buffalo The board kicks in from Playin' on down and it is another typically good 'upstate' show like the next night. 
Playin', China Rider, Greatest, Truckin>Eyes are pretty decent.
Charlie Clean this one up.  Highlights: Jam out of Truckin

The jam outta Truckin' This audience portion of this show is virtually unlistenable, but the sbd portion kicks before Playin' commences. The recording is marred a bit by a hum, but is altogether quite listenable.  Get this portion for the jam that developments out of Truckin'.  Unique '73 sound.
1st set sound quality Didn’t know Healy was recording soundboards in ‘73!
